Do you remember as a child sitting glued to the TV watching The Lion King? The mixed feelings it evoked in your young heart, the tears when Simba lost Mufasa, the excitement Timon and Pumbaa brought Simba, the suspense caused by the scary Scar, the intense battle of who will rule Pride Rock. This iconic movie made a huge impact on most childhoods.   If you haven’t watched this movie, the time is definitely now as they have recreated it in HD. It will premiere on July,19, and movies@ Emnotweni is giving you the chance to watch this iconic movie in 3D. Movies@ Emnotweni will be giving away tickets to the first 67 people who come at the following show times to watch The Lion King for the whole weekend. The tickets will be available 45 minutes prior to the shows on Friday, Saturday and Sunday at these two time slots: 12:00 and 17:00.   King Mufasa, leader of Pride Rock, has a cub called Simba who adores his father. All seems to be well at Pride Rock, but Mufasa’s brother, Scar, and former heir to the throne, is not happy about Simba’s arrival and plans to take Pride Rock for himself.  The battle for Pride Rock is ravaged with betrayal, tragedy and drama, ultimately resulting in Simba’s exile. With help from a curious pair of newfound friends, he will have to figure out how to grow up and take back what is rightfully his.  The Lion King is directed by Jon Favreau and has an amazing cast consisting of Seth Rogen, Beyoncé Knowles-Carter, Donald Glover, Chiwetel Ejiofor, Alfre Woodard, Billy Eichner and James Earl Jones.   